True, they will be provided with tools to be able to choose for themselves what type of material is being shown to them, reports the BBC.
"As we provide more and more control options for people, we will also start to show ads to those who use advertising lock-in software", said Andrew Bosworth, Vice-President of the Business of Facebook ads.
In other words, users will be able to choose what type of ads they see by selecting brands and industries that they find interesting.
"People don't like to see ads that don't apply to them or interfere with the content," said Bosworth.
Advertising blocking tools on mobile devices usually do not work, from which Facebook derives the biggest visit, but their reduction in banner exposure is also measured in billions of money.
According to the BBC, advertising blockers are used by around 200 million people.
As reported earlier in the quarter of the business year, Facebook's advertising revenues were USD 6.2 billion or EUR 5.55 billion.
It has to be said that this is not the first time Facebook has been actively involved in determining what network users see in their news streams.
As one of the last steps, Facebook has just started to take action to remove or at least limit from the news streams the headlines behind which are actually "empty" messages.
